## Vercel Speed Insights Configuration Completed

### Summary
Successfully configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js project by following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

### Changes Made

#### Modified Files:
1. **app/layout.tsx**
   - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag
   - The import statement was already present but the component wasn't being rendered
   - Followed the official Next.js App Router pattern from Vercel's documentation

2. **package-lock.json**
   - Updated lock file after running `npm install` to ensure @vercel/speed-insights is properly installed
   - The package was listed in package.json but dependencies weren't installed

### Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide for Next.js App Router projects:

```tsx
<body className="min-h-full flex flex-col">
  {children}
  <SpeedInsights />
</body>
```

This is the recommended pattern where:
- The SpeedInsights component is placed at the end of the body tag
- It automatically tracks Core Web Vitals (CLS, FID, LCP, FCP, TTFB, INP)
- The component uses `@vercel/speed-insights/next` for Next.js optimization

### Verification Steps Completed

✓ Dependencies installed successfully (npm install)
✓ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
✓ Linter passed with no errors (npm run lint)
✓ TypeScript compilation succeeded

### Next Steps

To enable Speed Insights in production:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Speed Insights tab in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click the "Enable" button if not already enabled
4. Speed Insights will start collecting data after deployment and user visits

